Interface RDMLoginMsgCallback

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    ConsumerCallback, NIProviderCallback, ProviderCallback
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Consumer, NIProvider, Provider, QueueConsumer, WatchlistConsumer

    public interface RDMLoginMsgCallback
    The RDM login message callback is used to communicate login message events to the application.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      int rdmLoginMsgCallback(RDMLoginMsgEvent event)
      A callback function that the Reactor will use to communicate login message events to the application.

    • Method Detail

      • rdmLoginMsgCallback

        int rdmLoginMsgCallback(RDMLoginMsgEvent event)
        A callback function that the Reactor will use to communicate login message events to the application.
        Parameters:
        event - A ReactorMsgEvent containing event information. The ReactorMsgEvent is valid only during callback
        Returns:
        ReactorCallbackReturnCodes A callback return code that can trigger specific Reactor behavior based on the outcome of the callback function
        See Also:
        RDMLoginMsgEvent, ReactorCallbackReturnCodes
